{
  "stem": "13623.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 495.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were put in charge to watch us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were liberated already.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We could not get out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "A day or two later, they were withdrawn.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We're going-- we're-- we're moving around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We know we can get out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I'll not-- I'll never forget.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When I got out of the gate, I was first of all-- I was afraid to-- I knew I was liberated.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I was afraid to walk out that gate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And every time I walk-- when I walk out that gate, I kept looking back if somebody is after me to take me back in.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We see English bulldozers making big, big graves.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We see captured our former guards, captured SS, loading dead bodies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The bodies were stacked up like a hill, high up, and they were loading them on trucks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the trucks were just like a dump truck.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The trucks would just dump them into the-- into the mass big grave that the bulldozers were-- were digging and the bodies fell down with the hands, legs dangling.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It would be like-- you didn't-- we were so hardened and watched this like you were watching mannequins being buried.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We also had former soldiers in the camps with us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Russian prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They-- they knew how to handle weapons and how to-- and they took eventually some of the SS.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They were-- they captured some of these SS and they were-- they killed them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Beat them to death.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And after a while, these things subsided.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They made all kinds of pictures.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I remember the British, there must have been a news photographer, news reel people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They took pictures of us, but I don't know whatever happened to these pictures.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
